                                                   India assured of 2nd spot in Tests

      A STAFF REPORTER
           
	Calcutta: The historic win in Perth has assured India a second place in the LG ICC Test Championship table behind Australia regardless of how the fourth and final Test in Adelaide Oval pans out. The Man of the Match in Indias 72-run win over Australia, Irfan Pathan, gained a lot in the latest ICC rankings released Sunday. 
    
	If the final Test is a draw, India will move two ratings points ahead of third-placed Sri Lanka and if Kumbles men square the series, they will finish on 113 ratings points, four ahead of Mahela Jayawardenas side. 
    
	If Australia win the match in Adelaide, India will sit above Sri Lanka when ratings points are calculated beyond the decimal point. 
    
	Tendulkar and Dravid rose one place each and now occupy on 13th and 15th positions respectively. Laxman climbed one place to 17th, while Sehwag jumped three places to share 32nd place with Pakistans Kamran Akmal and Englands Marcus Trescothick. 
    
